## PHASE 1: VISUAL FORENSICS (THE "ALAÏA" DNA)

### 1. The "Anti-Grid" Layout

**Principle:** Reject uniform, predictable grids. Embrace asymmetry and visual rhythm.

**Implementation:**
- **Masonry/Lookbook Layout:** Mix aspect ratios within a single grid system
  - **Row 1:** Single column hero image (full-width, variable height)
  - **Row 2:** Two columns (portrait-oriented images, 1:1.5 or 1:2 aspect ratio)
  - **Row 3:** Three columns (detail shots, square or 4:3 aspect ratio)
  - **Row 4:** Return to single column or mix of 2+1 columns

**Technical Specifications:**
```css
/* Example Grid Configuration */
.lookbook-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(12, 1fr);
  gap: 2.5rem 2.5rem; /* gap-x-10, gap-y-24 equivalent */
}

.hero-item {
  grid-column: 1 / -1; /* Full width */
}

.portrait-item {
  grid-column: span 6; /* Two columns */
}

.detail-item {
  grid-column: span 4; /* Three columns */
}
```

**Visual Rules:**
- Never use a perfect 4x4 grid
- Vary image sizes to create visual interest
- Allow images to "breathe" with generous gaps
- Maintain consistent vertical rhythm despite varied widths

