### 2. Hover Physics for Product Cards

**Principle:** Hover interactions should feel intentional and elegant, not gimmicky.

#### Image Swap (Back View)

**Behavior:** On hover, the primary product image transitions to a secondary view (back, detail, or alternative angle).

**Implementation:**
```jsx
// React Example
import { useState } from 'react';

const ProductCard = ({ primaryImage, secondaryImage, title, price }) => {
  const [isHovered, setIsHovered] = useState(false);

  return (
    <div
      className="product-card"
      onMouseEnter={() => setIsHovered(true)}
      onMouseLeave={() => setIsHovered(false)}
    >
      <div className="product-image-container">
        <img
          src={isHovered ? secondaryImage : primaryImage}
          alt={title}
          className="product-image"
        />
      </div>
      <div className="product-info">
        <h3>{title}</h3>
        <p className="price">{price}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};
```

**CSS Transition:**
```css
.product-image-container {
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;
  aspect-ratio: 3 / 4; /* Portrait ratio */
}

.product-image {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  transition: opacity 0.4s ease-in-out;
}

/* Alternative: Cross-fade effect */
.product-image-container::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  background-image: url('secondary-image.jpg');
  opacity: 0;
  transition: opacity 0.4s ease-in-out;
}

.product-card:hover .product-image-container::before {
  opacity: 1;
}
```

**Animation Details:**
- **Duration:** `0.4s ease-in-out`
- **Effect:** Cross-fade (opacity transition) or slide (transform)
- **Easing:** `cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)`

